description:
Responsibilities:


Assist manager in executing the merchant banking solutions, including cold call, negotiation, client relationship management, client due diligence and client audit;
Provide general office administration support including purchasing and procurement, document management, etc;
Recording and review of vendor invoices in the system;
Conduct other ad-hoc supporting duties.

Requirements:

Diploma/ Associate Degree or above;
At least 1 year of working experience, fresh graduates are also welcomed;
Experiences in customer service of banking are preferred;
Strong sense of maturity, responsibility, integrity and attention to detail;
Strong interpersonal and communication skills with fluency in English, Cantonese and Mandarin. Other Asian language is a plus.

Applications:

Interested parties please send your full resume giving details of current & expected salary and availability by clicking "Apply Now".

 *Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

The applicant must possess

a recognised degree in legal / accounting / finance or other related discipline;
a minimum of 3 years’ post-qualification work experience, preferably in law enforcement or finance and accounting or quantity surveying duties;
experience in NGOs or handling levy reporting or law enforcement is an advantage;
track record in system implementation is a plus;
be proactive with strong critical mind to continuously improve levy operation;
high level of integrity and sense of responsibility;
excellent analytical, communication and leadership skills with detailed mind;
proficiency in Microsoft application software (including Word, Excel and PowerPoint, etc.) as well as Chinese word processing; and
good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese.
(Applicants who do not possess the required qualifications and / or experience may be considered for other positions within the organisation.)
Duties include

Report to the Manager – Finance, the incumbent is expected:

to perform levy inspection and prepare documents on potential offence cases;
to collect evidence, take statements for investigation of non-compliant cases and to serve as prosecution witness in legal proceedings;
to prepare and continuously improve reports to maintain strong corporate governance on levy;
to work with IT and other parties for system upgrade;
to handle levy related documents including levy forms, eForms, eServices accounts and web submissions;
to prepare levy assessment to contractors;
to follow up levy issues with contractors and authorized persons;
to answer enquiries from levy payers and relevant parties;
to perform data input and payment receipts in levy collection system; and
to carry out any other duties as assigned from time to time by the Executive Director.
Applications:
The position is on a renewable fixed-term contract (subject to performance and operational needs) for a period of 2 years. 
Please click the below “Apply Online” to complete the application form and upload the updated curriculum vitae, the results of English and Chinese Language obtained in public examinations, current and expected salary together with a covering letter stating one’s suitability for the job on or before 21 January 2022. 
For further details on CIC please refer to website: http://www.cic.hk.

The incumbent will be responsible for monitoring receivable aging and ensure timely collection of outstanding debts, performing credit assessment to existing and new credit applications with the established guidelines, ensure timely and efficient resolution of all queries, both internal and external, Issue monthly debtors' statements and subsequent demand letters, preparing AR aging reports and ad hoc assignment.

High Diploma or Graduated in Accounting, Business Administration, or related disciplines;
3-4 years of solid working experience in Account Receivable;
Customer oriented with good inter-personal and communication skills;
Good Command of written and spoken English and Chinese.
Independent, proactive, detail-oriented and able to work under pressure
Proficiency in MS applications, especially MS Office and Excel & VBA;

Interested candidates please send your resume by email or clicking “Apply Now”.

We are equal opportunities employer. Applicants who are not invited within 2 months may consider their application unsuccessful. All applicants may be considered for other suitable positions with DCH Group / CITIC Pacific Group and will be deleted from our files after 6 months from the date of application.

Duties & responsibilities:

Prepare credit proposal for management review and approval;
Prepare reports for Credit Committee meeting;
Monitor client positions on wide range of products, including securities and derivatives products;
Conduct margin calls and ensure all trades transacted comply with the credit control policies;
Participate in various system enhancements and projects implementation to meet business demands.

Requirements:

Bachelor Degree holder in Finance, Business or related discipline;
Possess good knowledge in financial products, such as Bonds, Equity and index / commodities future etc.;
Relevant experience, preferably in banking / Financial institution;
A good team player, quick learner, self-motivated with strong sense of responsibility and discipline;
Good command of written and spoken English, Chinese and Mandarin;

We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits including 5-day week to the right candidate.  Interested parties please send your application letter with resume stating present and expected salary to Human Resources Department by clicking "Apply Now", or mail to Level 17, 28 Hennessy Road, Hong Kong. (Please quote the reference of the post on the envelope) .
All information received will be kept in strict confidence and only for recruitment-related purposes.

